    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n<title>Abstract Syntax Tree Interactive Explorer</title>\n<style>\n  /* Minimal styling: only default browser styles */\n  body {\n    font-family: monospace, monospace;\n    margin: 10px;\n    white-space: pre-wrap;\n  }\n  textarea, input[type=text], select, button {\n    font-family: monospace, monospace;\n    font-size: 14px;\n    margin: 3px 0;\n    width: 100%;\n    box-sizing: border-box;\n  }\n  label {\n    margin-top: 10px;\n    display: block;\n  }\n  #astContainer {\n    max-height: 400px;\n    overflow-y: auto;\n    border: 1px solid #000;\n    padding: 5px;\n    margin-top: 10px;\n  }\n  details {\n    margin-left: 20px;\n  }\n  summary {\n    cursor: pointer;\n    user-select: none;\n  }\n  button {\n    width: auto;\n    margin-right: 5px;\n  }\n  #info {\n    margin-top: 10px;\n  }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n\n<h1>Abstract Syntax Tree Interactive Explorer</h1>\n\n<label for=\"codeInput\">Enter JavaScript code (small snippets recommended):</label>\n<textarea id=\"codeInput\" rows=\"8\" spellcheck=\"false\">// Example: function add(a, b) { return a + b; }\n</textarea>\n\n<div>\n  <button id=\"parseBtn\">Parse Code → Generate AST</button>\n  <button id=\"resetBtn\">Reset</button>\n</div>\n\n<label for=\"modeSelect\">AST View Mode:</label>\n<select id=\"modeSelect\" title=\"Choose how the AST nodes are displayed\">\n  <option value=\"full\">Full Node Details (Type + Properties)</option>\n  <option value=\"typeOnly\" selected>Type Only</option>\n  <option value=\"summary\">Summary (Type + Key Info)</option>\n</select>\n\n<label for=\"expandLevelSlider\">Initial Expand Level (0 = collapsed, 5 = fully expanded): <span id=\"expandLevelValue\">2</span></label>\n<input type=\"range\" id=\"expandLevelSlider\" min=\"0\" max=\"5\" value=\"2\" />\n\n<label for=\"filterInput\">Filter Nodes (by type or property value, case-insensitive):</label>\n<input type=\"text\" id=\"filterInput\" placeholder=\"e.g. Identifier, Literal, +, return\" />\n\n<div>\n  <button id=\"expandAllBtn\">Expand All Visible</button>\n  <button id=\"collapseAllBtn\">Collapse All Visible</button>\n  <button id=\"highlightBtn\">Highlight Filter Matches</button>\n  <button id=\"clearHighlightBtn\">Clear Highlights</button>\n</div>\n\n<label for=\"nodeSelector\">Jump to Node by ID:</label>\n<input type=\"text\" id=\"nodeSelector\" placeholder=\"Enter node ID (e.g. n10)\" />\n<button id=\"gotoNodeBtn\">Go</button>\n\n<div id=\"astContainer\" aria-live=\"polite\" aria-label=\"AST display area\" tabindex=\"0\" role=\"region\"></div>\n\n<div id=\"info\" aria-live=\"assertive\" role=\"alert\" style=\"min-height:2em;\"></div>\n\n<hr />\n\n<h2>Interactive AST Node Inspector</h2>\n\n<label for=\"selectedNodeId\">Selected Node ID:</label>\n<input type=\"text\" id=\"selectedNodeId\" readonly />\n\n<label for=\"selectedNodeType\">Node Type:</label>\n<input type=\"text\" id=\"selectedNodeType\" readonly />\n\n<label for=\"selectedNodeValue\">Node Value / Key Property:</label>\n<input type=\"text\" id=\"selectedNodeValue\" readonly />\n\n<label for=\"editPropertySelect\">Select Property to Edit:</label>\n<select id=\"editPropertySelect\" disabled>\n  <option value=\"\">-- no property --</option>\n</select>\n\n<label for=\"editPropertyInput\">Edit Property Value:</label>\n<input type=\"text\" id=\"editPropertyInput\" disabled />\n\n<div>\n  <button id=\"applyEditBtn\" disabled>Apply Edit</button>\n  <button id=\"undoEditBtn\" disabled>Undo Last Edit</button>\n</div>\n\n<div>\n  <button id=\"serializeBtn\">Serialize AST to JSON</button>\n  <button id=\"downloadBtn\" disabled>Download JSON</button>\n</div>\n\n<hr />\n\n<h2>Help & Instructions</h2>\n<ul>\n  <li>Enter JavaScript code above and click \"Parse Code\" to generate the AST.</li>\n  <li>Use \"AST View Mode\" and \"Initial Expand Level\" to control display details.</li>\n  <li>Filter displayed nodes by typing in the filter box and pressing \"Highlight Filter Matches\".</li>\n  <li>Click on node summaries in the tree to select nodes and inspect/edit properties below.</li>\n  <li>After editing, apply changes or undo edits. Serialize and download the AST anytime.</li>\n  <li>The AST node tree uses &lt;details&gt; elements for expand/collapse. Keys and values can be inspected.</li>\n  <li>The interface supports deep interaction paths with node filtering, selection, editing, and serialization.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<script>\n(() => {\n  // Minimal parser / AST generator:\n  // We will use Acorn JavaScript parser to generate real AST.\n  // Because external libraries not allowed, build a minimal JS parser for demonstration:\n  // But it's complicated - instead, implement a minimal example parser for arithmetic expressions with variables and functions:\n  // For maximal richness, include a hand-crafted parser for limited JS expressions (like expressions only)\n  // However, prompt says \"focus on abstraction trees\" not real parsing.\n  // So, we will use the built-in Function constructor to parse code and create an AST with Esprima-like keys (simulate minimal AST).\n  //\n  // Since no external libraries allowed and prompt prohibits any external network or libraries, we must build a very limited JS AST generator.\n  //\n  // To allow maximal interactivity, we assume input is JS code and use Function.toString() and self-made minimal parse from tokenization.\n  // For demo purposes, we'll generate a very coarse AST:\n  //\n  // We'll:\n  //   - tokenize input by splitting on whitespace and punctuation,\n  //   - categorize tokens,\n  //   - support function declarations, variable declarations, return statements, expressions with +, -, *, /\n  //   - build a small AST.\n  //\n  // This rough parser is not complete or proper but sufficient for demo interactivity.\n\n  // The AST node ids generator:\n  let nodeIdCounter = 1;\n  function genNodeId() {\n    return 'n' + (nodeIdCounter++);\n  }\n\n  // Node Constructor:\n  function AstNode(type, props = {}) {\n    this.id = genNodeId();\n    this.type = type;\n    Object.assign(this, props);\n  }\n\n  // --- Tokenizer ---\n  function tokenize(input) {\n    // Split by JS reserved words, identifiers, literals, operators, punctuators\n    // We'll use a RegExp to extract tokens:\n\n    // For demo support keywords: function, return, var, let, const, if, else, for, while\n    // Support operators: + - * / = ; ( ) { } , < > <= >= == === != !==\n\n    // Token regex parts:\n    const regexs = [\n      {type: 'whitespace', regex: /^[ \\t\\r\\n]+/},\n      {type: 'number', regex: /^\\d+(\\.\\d+)?/},\n      {type: 'string', regex: /^('(\\\\'|[^'])*'|\"(\\\\\\\"|[^\"])*\")/},\n      {type: 'identifier', regex: /^[a-zA-Z_$][a-zA-Z0-9_$]*/},\n      {type: 'operator', regex: /^(\\+|\\-|\\*|\\/|=|<|>|<=|>=|==|===|!=|!==)/},\n      {type: 'punctuator', regex: /^(\\{|\\}|\\(|\\)|;|,)/},\n      {type: 'unknown', regex: /^.+?/},\n    ];\n\n    let pos = 0;\n    const tokens = [];\n\n    while (pos < input.length) {\n      let match = null;\n      for (const tokenDef of regexs) {\n        match = tokenDef.regex.exec(input.slice(pos));\n        if (match && match[0].length > 0) {\n          if (tokenDef.type !== 'whitespace') {\n            tokens.push({type: tokenDef.type, value: match[0], pos});\n          }\n          pos += match[0].length;\n          break;\n        }\n      }\n      if (!match) {\n        // No progress\n        tokens.push({type: 'unknown', value: input[pos], pos});\n        pos++;\n      }\n    }\n    return tokens;\n  }\n\n  // --- Parser ---\n  // Basic recursive descent parser for a tiny subset of JS (functions, var/let/const, return, binary expressions, identifiers, literals)\n  //\n  // Grammar (partial, simplified):\n  // Program := StatementList\n  // StatementList := Statement*\n  // Statement := FunctionDeclaration | VariableDeclaration | ExpressionStatement | ReturnStatement | BlockStatement\n  // FunctionDeclaration := 'function' Identifier '(' ParameterList ')' BlockStatement\n  // ParameterList := Identifier (',' Identifier)*\n  // VariableDeclaration := ('var'|'let'|'const') Identifier ('=' Expression)? ';'\n  // ReturnStatement := 'return' Expression? ';'\n  // ExpressionStatement := Expression ';'\n  // Expression := BinaryExpression | Identifier | Literal | FunctionCall\n  // BinaryExpression := Expression Operator Expression (only left-associative, no precedence for demo)\n  // FunctionCall := Identifier '(' ArgumentList ')'\n  // ArgumentList := Expression (',' Expression)*\n  // BlockStatement := '{' StatementList '}'\n  // Identifier := as token.type === 'identifier'\n  // Literal := number or string token\n  //\n\n  // Parsing helper utilities:\n  function Parser(tokens) {\n    this.tokens = tokens;\n    this.pos = 0;\n  }\n\n  Parser.prototype.peek = function() {\n    return this.tokens[this.pos];\n  };\n\n  Parser.prototype.next = function() {\n    return this.tokens[this.pos++];\n  };\n\n  Parser.prototype.eof = function() {\n    return this.pos >= this.tokens.length;\n  };\n\n  Parser.prototype.expect = function(type, value) {\n    const token = this.peek();\n    if (!token || token.type !== type || (value !== undefined && token.value !== value)) {\n      throw new Error(`Expected token type ${type}${value!==undefined?' with value '+value:''} at position ${token?token.pos:'EOF'}`);\n    }\n    return this.next();\n  };\n\n  // Consume optional punctuation:\n  Parser.prototype.consumeIf = function(type, value) {\n    const token = this.peek();\n    if (token && token.type === type && (value===undefined || token.value === value)) {\n      this.next();\n      return true;\n    }\n    return false;\n  };\n\n  // Parse Program\n  Parser.prototype.parseProgram = function() {\n    const body = [];\n    while (!this.eof()) {\n      const stmt = this.parseStatement();\n      if (stmt) body.push(stmt);\n      else break;\n    }\n    return new AstNode('Program', {body});\n  };\n\n  Parser.prototype.parseStatement = function() {\n    const token = this.peek();\n    if (!token) return null;\n    if (token.type === 'identifier' && token.value === 'function') {\n      return this.parseFunctionDeclaration();\n    } else if (token.type === 'identifier' && (token.value === 'var' || token.value === 'let' || token.value === 'const')) {\n      return this.parseVariableDeclaration();\n    } else if (token.type === 'identifier' && token.value === 'return') {\n      return this.parseReturnStatement();\n    } else if (token.type === 'punctuator' && token.value === '{') {\n      return this.parseBlockStatement();\n    } else {\n      return this.parseExpressionStatement();\n    }\n  };\n\n  Parser.prototype.parseFunctionDeclaration = function() {\n    this.expect('identifier','function');\n    const id = this.parseIdentifier();\n    this.expect('punctuator','(');\n    const params = this.parseParameterList();\n    this.expect('punctuator',')');\n    const body = this.parseBlockStatement();\n    return new AstNode('FunctionDeclaration', {id, params, body});\n  };\n\n  Parser.prototype.parseParameterList = function() {\n    const params = [];\n    if (this.consumeIf('punctuator',')')) {\n      this.pos--;\n      return params;\n    }\n    while(true) {\n      const param = this.parseIdentifier();\n      params.push(param);\n      if (!this.consumeIf('punctuator',',')) break;\n    }\n    return params;\n  };\n\n  Parser.prototype.parseVariableDeclaration = function() {\n    const kindToken = this.next(); // var|let|const\n    const kind = kindToken.value;\n    const declarations = [];\n    while(true) {\n      const id = this.parseIdentifier();\n      let init = null;\n      if (this.consumeIf('operator','=')) {\n        init = this.parseExpression();\n      }\n      declarations.push(new AstNode('VariableDeclarator', {id, init}));\n      if (!this.consumeIf('punctuator',',')) break;\n    }\n    this.expect('punctuator',';');\n    return new AstNode('VariableDeclaration', {kind, declarations});\n  };\n\n  Parser.prototype.parseReturnStatement = function() {\n    this.expect('identifier','return');\n    let argument = null;\n    if (!this.consumeIf('punctuator',';')) {\n      argument = this.parseExpression();\n      this.expect('punctuator',';');\n    }\n    return new AstNode('ReturnStatement', {argument});\n  };\n\n  Parser.prototype.parseBlockStatement = function() {\n    this.expect('punctuator','{');\n    const body = [];\n    while(!this.consumeIf('punctuator','}')) {\n      if(this.eof()) throw new Error('Unclosed block statement');\n      const stmt = this.parseStatement();\n      if (stmt) body.push(stmt);\n      else break;\n    }\n    return new AstNode('BlockStatement', {body});\n  };\n\n  Parser.prototype.parseExpressionStatement = function() {\n    const expr = this.parseExpression();\n    this.expect('punctuator',';');\n    return new AstNode('ExpressionStatement', {expression: expr});\n  };\n\n  Parser.prototype.parseExpression = function() {\n    // Parse left-associative binary expression without precedence for demo:\n    let left = this.parsePrimaryExpression();\n    while(true) {\n      const token = this.peek();\n      if (token && token.type === 'operator' && ['+', '-', '*', '/'].includes(token.value)) {\n        const op = this.next().value;\n        const right = this.parsePrimaryExpression();\n        left = new AstNode('BinaryExpression', {operator: op, left, right});\n      } else {\n        break;\n      }\n    }\n    return left;\n  };\n\n  Parser.prototype.parsePrimaryExpression = function() {\n    const token = this.peek();\n    if (!token) throw new Error(\"Unexpected EOF in expression\");\n    if (token.type === 'identifier') {\n      // Check for function call\n      const id = this.parseIdentifier();\n      if (this.consumeIf('punctuator','(')) {\n        const args = this.parseArgumentList();\n        this.expect('punctuator',')');\n        return new AstNode('CallExpression', {callee: id, arguments: args});\n      }\n      return id;\n    } else if (token.type === 'number') {\n      return this.parseLiteral();\n    } else if (token.type === 'string') {\n      return this.parseLiteral();\n    } else if (token.type === 'punctuator' && token.value === '(') {\n      this.next();\n      const expr = this.parseExpression();\n      this.expect('punctuator',')');\n      return expr;\n    } else {\n      throw new Error(`Unexpected token ${token.type} ${token.value} at position ${token.pos}`);\n    }\n  };\n\n  Parser.prototype.parseArgumentList = function() {\n    const args = [];\n    if (this.peek() && this.peek().type === 'punctuator' && this.peek().value === ')') {\n      return args;\n    }\n    while(true) {\n      const expr = this.parseExpression();\n      args.push(expr);\n      if (!this.consumeIf('punctuator',',')) break;\n    }\n    return args;\n  };\n\n  Parser.prototype.parseIdentifier = function() {\n    const token = this.expect('identifier');\n    return new AstNode('Identifier', {name: token.value});\n  };\n\n  Parser.prototype.parseLiteral = function() {\n    const token = this.next();\n    return new AstNode('Literal', {value: token.type === 'number' ? Number(token.value) : token.value.slice(1,-1)});\n  };\n\n  // --- End of parser ---\n\n  // --- AST Tree Rendering and interaction ---\n\n  // We will generate DOM tree using <details> and <summary> per node, indenting nested nodes with HTML hierarchy.\n\n  // Store AST globally:\n  let astRoot = null;\n\n  // Store edits history stack:\n  const editHistory = [];\n\n  // Current selected node:\n  let selectedNode = null;\n\n  // Map from node id to dom node & data\n  const idToNode = new Map();\n\n  // === AST Renderer Functions ===\n\n  // Mode: \"full\" : show full details of each node including all props and values\n  // Mode: \"typeOnly\" : show only node type label in summary\n  // Mode: \"summary\" : show type plus key prop or short summary (like for Identifier show name, for Literal show value)\n\n  // We support expanding levels (initial open depth). Use recursion position.\n\n  // Filter: function(node) -> boolean to decide if node matches filter or contains matches\n\n  // Highlights: highlight matched nodes in filter\n\n  const astContainer = document.getElementById('astContainer');\n  const info = document.getElementById('info');\n\n  // Simple utility, sort object keys alphabetically for consistent order\n  function sortedKeys(obj) {\n    return Object.keys(obj).sort();\n  }\n\n  // Function to check if an object is an AST Node (has 'type' and 'id' props)\n  function isAstNode(obj) {\n    return obj && typeof obj === 'object' && typeof obj.type === 'string' && typeof obj.id === 'string';\n  }\n\n  // Find a short preview string for node key info:\n  function previewNodeSummary(node) {\n    if (!node || typeof node !== 'object') return '';\n    try {\n      switch(node.type) {\n        case 'Identifier':\n          return node.name;\n        case 'Literal':\n          return JSON.stringify(node.value);\n        case 'VariableDeclarator':\n          return node.id ? ('id: ' + (node.id.name || node.id.type || '?')) : '';\n        case 'FunctionDeclaration':\n          if (node.id && node.id.name) return node.id.name + '(...)';\n          return 'function(...)';\n        case 'BinaryExpression':\n          return node.operator || '';\n        case 'CallExpression':\n          return node.callee ? (node.callee.name || node.callee.type) + '(...)' : 'call(...)';\n        case 'VariableDeclaration':\n          return node.kind || '';\n        case 'ReturnStatement':\n          return node.argument ? previewNodeSummary(node.argument) : '';\n        default:\n          // Try to find first property that is string or number or literal\n          for (const key of sortedKeys(node)) {\n            const val = node[key];\n            if (typeof val === 'string' && val.length < 20) return val;\n            if (typeof val === 'number') return String(val);\n            if (typeof val === 'object' && val !== null && val.type) return previewNodeSummary(val);\n          }\n          return '';\n      }\n    } catch(e) {\n      return '';\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Highlight and unhighlight utility\n  function highlightNodeSummary(summaryEl) {\n    summaryEl.style.fontWeight = 'bold';\n    summaryEl.style.textDecoration = 'underline';\n  }\n  function clearHighlightNodeSummary(summaryEl) {\n    summaryEl.style.fontWeight = '';\n    summaryEl.style.textDecoration = '';\n  }\n\n  // Clear all highlights\n  function clearAllHighlights() {\n    idToNode.forEach(({summaryEl}) => {\n      if (summaryEl) clearHighlightNodeSummary(summaryEl);\n    });\n  }\n\n  // DOM renderer recursive function:\n\n  // Parameters:\n  // node: AstNode\n  // mode: string (\"full\", \"typeOnly\", \"summary\")\n  // expandLevel: number (initial expand depth, >=0)\n  // currentDepth: number(used internally)\n  // filter: function(node) => boolean or null\n  // returns DOM element (<details> or text node)\n\n  function renderAstNode(node, mode, expandLevel, currentDepth, filter) {\n    // Check node is AstNode\n    if (!isAstNode(node)) return document.createTextNode('');\n\n    // Filter: We want to show node if it matches filter or any of its descendants matches filter,\n    // else hide it (return null or empty text)\n\n    const matchesFilter = filter ? filter(node) : true;\n\n    // Recursively check children for filter:\n    let childVisible = false;\n    const childrenNodes = [];\n\n    for (const key of sortedKeys(node)) {\n      if (key === 'id' || key === 'type') continue;\n      const val = node[key];\n      if (val === null || val === undefined) continue;\n      if (Array.isArray(val)) {\n        for (const v of val) {\n          if (isAstNode(v)) {\n            const child = renderAstNode(v, mode, expandLevel, currentDepth + 1, filter);\n            if (child !== null) {\n              childVisible = true;\n              childrenNodes.push({key, node: v, el: child});\n            }\n          }\n        }\n      } else if (isAstNode(val)) {\n        const child = renderAstNode(val, mode, expandLevel, currentDepth + 1, filter);\n        if (child !== null) {\n          childVisible = true;\n          childrenNodes.push({key, node: val, el: child});\n        }\n      }\n    }\n\n    if (!matchesFilter && !childVisible) return null; // node filtered out completely\n\n    // Create <details> and <summary> for this node\n    const details = document.createElement('details');\n    details.setAttribute('data-id', node.id);\n    details.tabIndex = -1;\n\n    // Expand details if currentDepth < expandLevel\n    if (currentDepth < expandLevel) {\n      details.open = true;\n    }\n\n    const summary = document.createElement('summary');\n    summary.tabIndex = 0; // to allow focus\n    summary.textContent = '';\n\n    // Compose summary text according to mode:\n    if (mode === 'typeOnly') {\n      summary.textContent = node.type;\n    } else if (mode === 'summary') {\n      const shortInfo = previewNodeSummary(node);\n      summary.textContent = node.type + (shortInfo ? ' - ' + shortInfo : '');\n    } else if (mode === 'full') {\n      // Show type + all props\n      summary.textContent = node.type;\n    }\n\n    // Add summary attributes for accessibility and selection:\n    summary.title = 'Node ID: ' + node.id;\n\n    details.appendChild(summary);\n\n    // Save to map for selection and highlighting:\n    idToNode.set(node.id, {node, element: details, summaryEl: summary});\n\n    // If mode full, show all properties as subnodes:\n    if (mode === 'full') {\n      // Show all props as entries:\n      for (const key of sortedKeys(node)) {\n        if (key === 'id' || key === 'type') continue;\n        const val = node[key];\n        let propDetails = document.createElement('details');\n        propDetails.style.marginLeft = '1em';\n        let propSummary = document.createElement('summary');\n        propSummary.textContent = key;\n        propSummary.title = 'Property: ' + key;\n        propDetails.appendChild(propSummary);\n\n        if (val === null) {\n          const n = document.createTextNode('null');\n          propDetails.appendChild(n);\n        } else if (val === undefined) {\n          const n = document.createTextNode('undefined');\n          propDetails.appendChild(n);\n        } else if (Array.isArray(val)) {\n          if (val.length === 0) {\n            propDetails.appendChild(document.createTextNode('[ ]'));\n          } else {\n            for (let i = 0; i < val.length; i++) {\n              const e = val[i];\n              if (isAstNode(e)) {\n                const child = renderAstNode(e, mode, expandLevel, currentDepth + 2, filter);\n                if (child !== null) {\n                  propDetails.appendChild(child);\n                }\n              } else {\n                let textVal = (typeof e === 'string' ? '\"' + e + '\"' : String(e));\n                propDetails.appendChild(document.createTextNode(textVal));\n                propDetails.appendChild(document.createElement('br'));\n              }\n            }\n          }\n        } else if (isAstNode(val)) {\n          const child = renderAstNode(val, mode, expandLevel, currentDepth + 2, filter);\n          if (child !== null) propDetails.appendChild(child);\n        } else if (typeof val === 'object') {\n          // Plain object:\n          propDetails.appendChild(document.createTextNode(JSON.stringify(val)));\n        } else {\n          // Primitive value:\n          propDetails.appendChild(document.createTextNode(String(val)));\n        }\n        details.appendChild(propDetails);\n      }\n    } else {\n      // For other modes, render children nodes under details:\n      for (const child of childrenNodes) {\n        details.appendChild(child.el);\n      }\n    }\n\n    // Highlight filter matches if filter provided\n    if (filter && matchesFilter) {\n      summary.style.fontWeight = 'bold';\n      summary.style.textDecoration = 'underline';\n    }\n\n    return details;\n  }\n\n  // --- Filtering ---\n\n  // Return function to match node if any of node.type or string props or key props contain filter string\n  function buildFilterFunction(filterStr) {\n    if (!filterStr || filterStr.trim() === '') return null;\n    const frag = filterStr.trim().toLowerCase();\n    return function filter(node) {\n      // Check type\n      if (node.type.toLowerCase().includes(frag)) return true;\n      for (const key of sortedKeys(node)) {\n        const val = node[key];\n        if (val === null || val === undefined) continue;\n        if (typeof val === 'string' && val.toLowerCase().includes(frag)) return true;\n        if (typeof val === 'number' && String(val).includes(frag)) return true;\n        if (Array.isArray(val)) {\n          for (const e of val) {\n            if (e && typeof e === 'object') {\n              if (filter(e)) return true;\n            } else if (typeof e === 'string' && e.toLowerCase().includes(frag)) return true;\n          }\n        } else if (typeof val === 'object' && val !== null) {\n          if (filter(val)) return true;\n        }\n      }\n      return false;\n    };\n  }\n\n  // --- Selection and Node Inspector ---\n\n  // Elements:\n  const selectedNodeIdInput = document.getElementById('selectedNodeId');\n  const selectedNodeTypeInput = document.getElementById('selectedNodeType');\n  const selectedNodeValueInput = document.getElementById('selectedNodeValue');\n  const editPropertySelect = document.getElementById('editPropertySelect');\n  const editPropertyInput = document.getElementById('editPropertyInput');\n  const applyEditBtn = document.getElementById('applyEditBtn');\n  const undoEditBtn = document.getElementById('undoEditBtn');\n  const serializeBtn = document.getElementById('serializeBtn');\n  const downloadBtn = document.getElementById('downloadBtn');\n\n  // Selected property to edit:\n  let selectedPropertyKey = null;\n\n  // When a node is clicked in the tree, select it:\n  function onNodeSummaryClick(event) {\n    let summaryEl = event.target;\n    if (summaryEl.tagName !== 'SUMMARY') return;\n    const details = summaryEl.parentElement;\n    if (!details.hasAttribute('data-id')) return;\n    const nid = details.getAttribute('data-id');\n    selectNodeById(nid);\n  }\n\n  function selectNodeById(nid) {\n    const entry = idToNode.get(nid);\n    if (!entry) {\n      info.textContent = 'Node with ID \"' + nid + '\" not found.';\n      clearInspector();\n      return;\n    }\n    selectedNode = entry.node;\n    updateInspector();\n    info.textContent = 'Selected node ' + nid;\n  }\n\n  function clearInspector() {\n    selectedNodeIdInput.value = '';\n    selectedNodeTypeInput.value = '';\n    selectedNodeValueInput.value = '';\n    editPropertySelect.innerHTML = '<option value=\"\">-- no property --</option>';\n    editPropertySelect.disabled = true;\n    editPropertyInput.value = '';\n    editPropertyInput.disabled = true;\n    applyEditBtn.disabled = true;\n  }\n\n  function updateInspector() {\n    if (!selectedNode) {\n      clearInspector();\n      return;\n    }\n    selectedNodeIdInput.value = selectedNode.id || '';\n    selectedNodeTypeInput.value = selectedNode.type || '';\n    selectedNodeValueInput.value = previewNodeSummary(selectedNode) || '';\n\n    // Fill editPropertySelect with editable properties (strings and numbers only, excluding id and type)\n    editPropertySelect.innerHTML = '<option value=\"\">-- select property to edit --</option>';\n    let optionsExist = false;\n    for (const key of sortedKeys(selectedNode)) {\n      if (key === 'id' || key === 'type') continue;\n      const val = selectedNode[key];\n      if (typeof val === 'string' || typeof val === 'number') {\n        const opt = document.createElement('option');\n        opt.value = key;\n        opt.textContent = key + ': ' + val;\n        editPropertySelect.appendChild(opt);\n        optionsExist = true;\n      }\n    }\n\n    if (optionsExist) {\n      editPropertySelect.disabled = false;\n      // disable editing inputs until a property is chosen\n      editPropertyInput.value = '';\n      editPropertyInput.disabled = true;\n      applyEditBtn.disabled = true;\n    } else {\n      editPropertySelect.disabled = true;\n      editPropertyInput.value = '';\n      editPropertyInput.disabled = true;\n      applyEditBtn.disabled = true;\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Event for property select change:\n  editPropertySelect.addEventListener('change', () => {\n    selectedPropertyKey = editPropertySelect.value || null;\n    if (selectedPropertyKey && selectedNode) {\n      const val = selectedNode[selectedPropertyKey];\n      editPropertyInput.value = val;\n      editPropertyInput.disabled = false;\n      applyEditBtn.disabled = false;\n    } else {\n      editPropertyInput.value = '';\n      editPropertyInput.disabled = true;\n      applyEditBtn.disabled = true;\n    }\n  });\n\n  // Apply Edit button click:\n  applyEditBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    if (!selectedNode || !selectedPropertyKey) return;\n    const oldVal = selectedNode[selectedPropertyKey];\n    let newValRaw = editPropertyInput.value;\n\n    // Try to guess type:\n    let newVal;\n    if (typeof oldVal === 'number') {\n      newVal = Number(newValRaw);\n      if (isNaN(newVal)) {\n        info.textContent = 'Invalid number: ' + newValRaw;\n        return;\n      }\n    } else {\n      newVal = newValRaw;\n    }\n\n    // Record undo info:\n    editHistory.push({node: selectedNode, key: selectedPropertyKey, oldValue: oldVal, newValue: newVal});\n\n    // Apply\n    selectedNode[selectedPropertyKey] = newVal;\n    info.textContent = `Applied edit on node ${selectedNode.id}: ${selectedPropertyKey} = ${newValRaw}`;\n\n    // Refresh inspector display (in case preview changed)\n    updateInspector();\n\n    // Re-render AST display (to reflect change)\n    renderCurrentAst();\n\n    // Enable undo:\n    undoEditBtn.disabled = false;\n  });\n\n  // Undo last edit:\n  undoEditBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    if (editHistory.length === 0) {\n      info.textContent = 'Nothing to undo.';\n      undoEditBtn.disabled = true;\n      return;\n    }\n    const lastEdit = editHistory.pop();\n    lastEdit.node[lastEdit.key] = lastEdit.oldValue;\n    info.textContent = `Undid edit on node ${lastEdit.node.id}: ${lastEdit.key} restored to ${lastEdit.oldValue}`;\n\n    // Refresh inspector if current node affected:\n    if (selectedNode && selectedNode.id === lastEdit.node.id) {\n      updateInspector();\n    }\n\n    renderCurrentAst();\n\n    if (editHistory.length === 0) {\n      undoEditBtn.disabled = true;\n    }\n  });\n\n  // --- UI Controls & Events ---\n\n  const codeInput = document.getElementById('codeInput');\n  const parseBtn = document.getElementById('parseBtn');\n  const resetBtn = document.getElementById('resetBtn');\n  const modeSelect = document.getElementById('modeSelect');\n  const expandLevelSlider = document.getElementById('expandLevelSlider');\n  const expandLevelValue = document.getElementById('expandLevelValue');\n  const filterInput = document.getElementById('filterInput');\n  const expandAllBtn = document.getElementById('expandAllBtn');\n  const collapseAllBtn = document.getElementById('collapseAllBtn');\n  const highlightBtn = document.getElementById('highlightBtn');\n  const clearHighlightBtn = document.getElementById('clearHighlightBtn');\n  const nodeSelector = document.getElementById('nodeSelector');\n  const gotoNodeBtn = document.getElementById('gotoNodeBtn');\n\n  // Update expand level span:\n  expandLevelSlider.addEventListener('input', () => {\n    expandLevelValue.textContent = expandLevelSlider.value;\n  });\n\n  function renderCurrentAst() {\n    if (!astRoot) return;\n    idToNode.clear();\n    clearInspector();\n    selectedNode = null;\n\n    const mode = modeSelect.value;\n    const expandLevel = parseInt(expandLevelSlider.value, 10);\n    const filter = buildFilterFunction(filterInput.value);\n\n    // Because renderAstNode can return null when filtered out, handle that:\n    let renderedAst = renderAstNode(astRoot, mode, expandLevel, 0, filter);\n    if (!renderedAst) {\n      astContainer.textContent = 'No AST to display with current filter.';\n    } else {\n      astContainer.innerHTML = '';\n      astContainer.appendChild(renderedAst);\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Parse button handler:\n  parseBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    const code = codeInput.value;\n    if (!code.trim()) {\n      info.textContent = 'Please enter some code to parse.';\n      return;\n    }\n    try {\n      const tokens = tokenize(code);\n      nodeIdCounter = 1;\n      const parser = new Parser(tokens);\n      astRoot = parser.parseProgram();\n\n      info.textContent = 'Parsing succeeded. AST generated with root node ID ' + astRoot.id + '.';\n      editHistory.length = 0; // clear history\n      undoEditBtn.disabled = true;\n      downloadBtn.disabled = true;\n      renderCurrentAst();\n    } catch(e) {\n      info.textContent = 'Parse error: ' + e.message;\n      astContainer.textContent = '';\n      astRoot = null;\n      clearInspector();\n      editHistory.length = 0;\n      undoEditBtn.disabled = true;\n      downloadBtn.disabled = true;\n    }\n  });\n\n  // Reset button handler:\n  resetBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    codeInput.value = '';\n    astContainer.textContent = '';\n    info.textContent = 'Reset done.';\n    astRoot = null;\n    clearInspector();\n    editHistory.length = 0;\n    undoEditBtn.disabled = true;\n    downloadBtn.disabled = true;\n  });\n\n  // Mode select changes:\n  modeSelect.addEventListener('change', () => {\n    renderCurrentAst();\n  });\n\n  // Expand level changed:\n  expandLevelSlider.addEventListener('change', () => {\n    renderCurrentAst();\n  });\n\n  // Filter input change does not trigger automatic render to let user control highlight button\n  // Highlight filter matches button handler:\n  highlightBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    const filter = buildFilterFunction(filterInput.value);\n    if (!astRoot) {\n      info.textContent = 'No AST generated.';\n      return;\n    }\n    if (!filter) {\n      info.textContent = 'Please enter filter text.';\n      return;\n    }\n    clearAllHighlights();\n    let count = 0;\n    idToNode.forEach(({node, summaryEl}) => {\n      if (filter(node)) {\n        highlightNodeSummary(summaryEl);\n        count++;\n      }\n    });\n    info.textContent = 'Highlight done: ' + count + ' nodes matched filter.';\n  });\n\n  // Clear highlight:\n  clearHighlightBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    clearAllHighlights();\n    info.textContent = 'Highlights cleared.';\n  });\n\n  // Expand all visible button:\n  expandAllBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    idToNode.forEach(({element}) => {\n      element.open = true;\n    });\n  });\n\n  // Collapse all visible button:\n  collapseAllBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    idToNode.forEach(({element}) => {\n      element.open = false;\n    });\n  });\n\n  // Go to Node button:\n  gotoNodeBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    const nid = nodeSelector.value.trim();\n    if (!nid) {\n      info.textContent = 'Enter a node ID.';\n      return;\n    }\n    const entry = idToNode.get(nid);\n    if (!entry) {\n      info.textContent = 'Node ID \"' + nid + '\" not found.';\n      return;\n    }\n    // Expand all parent details to reveal node\n    let curr = entry.element;\n    while (curr && curr !== astContainer) {\n      if (curr.tagName === 'DETAILS') curr.open = true;\n      curr = curr.parentElement;\n    }\n    const rect = entry.element.getBoundingClientRect();\n    astContainer.scrollTop += rect.top - astContainer.getBoundingClientRect().top - 20;\n    // Select node\n    selectNodeById(nid);\n  });\n\n  // AST container click handler to select nodes on summary click\n  astContainer.addEventListener('click', onNodeSummaryClick);\n\n  // --- AST Serialization ---\n  function serializeAst(node) {\n    // Remove cyclic or circular refs, only keep valid properties, no functions\n    if (!node || typeof node !== 'object') return node;\n    if (Array.isArray(node)) return node.map(serializeAst);\n    const obj = {};\n    for (const key of Object.keys(node)) {\n      const val = node[key];\n      if (key === 'id') continue; // omit id in serialization to keep clean output, can be adjusted\n      if (typeof val === 'function') continue;\n      if (typeof val === 'object') {\n        obj[key] = serializeAst(val);\n      } else {\n        obj[key] = val;\n      }\n    }\n    obj.type = node.type; // always include type\n    return obj;\n  }\n\n  serializeBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    if (!astRoot) {\n      info.textContent = 'No AST to serialize.';\n      return;\n    }\n    try {\n      const ser = serializeAst(astRoot);\n      const jsonStr = JSON.stringify(ser, null, 2);\n      // Show jsonStr in a prompt or modal (since no styling, use prompt)\n      // But prompt only max few KB. Instead show in textarea below AST container\n      let existingArea = document.getElementById('jsonOutputArea');\n      if (!existingArea) {\n        existingArea = document.createElement('textarea');\n        existingArea.id = 'jsonOutputArea';\n        existingArea.rows = 20;\n        existingArea.readOnly = true;\n        existingArea.style.width = '100%';\n        existingArea.style.marginTop = '10px';\n        astContainer.parentElement.appendChild(existingArea);\n      }\n      existingArea.value = jsonStr;\n      info.textContent = 'AST serialized to JSON below. Use Download to save.';\n      downloadBtn.disabled = false;\n      // Store for download:\n      downloadBtn.dataset.json = jsonStr;\n    } catch(e) {\n      info.textContent = 'Serialization error: ' + e.message;\n    }\n  });\n\n  // Download button:\n  downloadBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    const jsonStr = downloadBtn.dataset.json;\n    if (!jsonStr) {\n      info.textContent = 'No JSON available to download.';\n      return;\n    }\n    const blob = new Blob([jsonStr], {type: 'application/json'});\n    const url = URL.createObjectURL(blob);\n    const a = document.createElement('a');\n    a.href = url;\n    a.download = 'ast.json';\n    a.click();\n    URL.revokeObjectURL(url);\n    info.textContent = 'AST JSON downloaded.';\n  });\n})();\n</script>\n\n</body>\n</html>"
